The paper deals with the problem of downlink channel state information (CSI) feedback in massive multiple-input multiple-output (MIMO) systems. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also proposes a deep learning (DL) approach to improve the efficiency of CSI feedback, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The DL approach is applied to wireless communication systems, which suggests the category of cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The proposed approach also involves an advanced training scheme, which can be categorized under cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper uses simulation results to demonstrate the effectiveness of the proposed approach, which can be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
